3. Make your changes and commit them: `git commit -m 'Add some feature'` or `git commit -m 'Fix a bug'`
4. Push to your branch: `git push origin feature/your-feature-name` or `git push origin bugfix/your-bug-fix`
5. Submit a pull request detailing your changes.

